<DOC><DOCNO> AP880801-0159 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-01-88 1941EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Plane-Robbery     08-01 0177</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Plane-Robbery,0183</SECOND><HEAD>Two Men Force Plane to Land, Steal Gold, Rob Passengers</HEAD><DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two men with pistols and grenades forcedan airliner to land on an abandoned runway Monday, where theyseized a gold shipment and robbed the 22 passengers, Medellinpolice said.   A police statement said the propeller-driven Twin Otter plane ofthe Colombian airline ACES was on a flight from the northwest townof El Bagre to the industrial city of Medellin when forced to landnear Campamento village, about 60 miles southwest of El Bagre.   Six other gunmen joined the two hijackers and took the gold andpassengers' jewelry, money and other valuables, the statement said.   The cargo of gold came from a mine near El Bagre and was valuedat $500,000, police said.   The gunmen smashed the plane's radio, kicked the co-pilot in theface, warned the pilot not to take off for an hour and then fledinto the jungle, police said.   The plane took off from the grass runway after an hour andlanded safely in Medellin.</TEXT></DOC>